systematic /ˌsɪstɪˈmætɪk/

1. ADJ Something that is done in a systematic way is done according to a fixed plan, in a thorough and efficient way. 有计划的 

例： They went about their business in a systematic way. 他们按部就班地做生意。 

2. systematically ADV 有计划地 

例： The army has systematically violated human rights. 军队已有计划地侵犯了人权。

</div>

